{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643110","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643110"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:49:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:49:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17985"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17985"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.14,0.25,0.32,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10699"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77641"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10699"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17985"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63154"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5100"},{"type":"tags","id":"10025"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24911"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24915"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77641"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes how metformin acts in the liver?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK activation","Increases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK inhibition","Decreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK inhibition","Increases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK activation","Increases hepatic glucose production through AMPK activation"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK activation\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer. Metformin activates AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK), which is a key regulator of energy balance. In the liver, AMPK activation leads to increased fatty acid oxidation and decreased lipogenesis, which can be beneficial in conditions like non-alcoholic fatty liver disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK activation\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because AMPK activation actually increases fatty acid oxidation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK inhibition\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because AMPK activation, not inhibition, is responsible for increasing fatty acid oxidation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreases hepatic fatty acid oxidation through AMPK inhibition\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because AMPK activation increases fatty acid oxidation, not decreases it.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases hepatic glucose production through AMPK activation\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because AMPK activation decreases hepatic glucose production, contributing to improved glycaemic control in diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Metformin activates AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK), which plays a role in increasing hepatic fatty acid oxidation.","Metformin is primarily used in the management of type 2 diabetes mellitus, but it also has effects on liver metabolism.","AMPK activation by metformin leads to decreased hepatic glucose production and increased insulin sensitivity."],"references":["Gilbert-Barness, E., Barness, L. A., \u0026 Farrell, P. M. (Eds.). (2017). Metabolic diseases: foundations of clinical management, genetics, and pathology. IOS Press","Lanham-New, S. A., Macdonald, I. A., \u0026 Roche, H. M. (Eds.). (2011). Nutrition and metabolism. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Roche, H. M., Macdonald, I. A., Schols, A. M., \u0026 Lanham-New, S. A. (Eds.). (2024). Nutrition and metabolism. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","LaMoia TE, Shulman GI. Cellular and Molecular Mechanisms of Metformin Action. Endocr Rev. 2021 Jan 28;42(1):77-96. doi: 10.1210/endrev/bnaa023. PMID: 32897388; PMCID: PMC7846086.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Rena G, Hardie DG, Pearson ER. The mechanisms of action of metformin. Diabetologia. 2017 Sep;60(9):1577-1585. doi: 10.1007/s00125-017-4342-z. Epub 2017 Aug 3. PMID: 28776086; PMCID: PMC5552828."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63154"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17985"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63154","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63154"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T20:55:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-08T00:06:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10699"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77641"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"met